00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:57,440
cried the future bride, in the middle 
of a flood of questions and sympathy.

193
00:18:58,080 --> 00:19:04,480
As she spoke, she eagerly took hold of the 
brown-paper parcel that was still under my arm.

194
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:09,840
'I advise you not to open 
it!' I cried. 'It's a salmon!'

195
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:15,200
The future bride gave a little scream of distaste,  

196
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:22,240
and without a moment's hesitation, threw it at 
her best friend, a girl standing near her. The  

197
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:29,120
best friend gave an answering scream, and jumped 
to one side. The parcel that I had looked after  

198
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:35,520
with a mother's care across two countries and a 
stormy sea fell with a crash on the stone floor.

199
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,480
Why did it crash?

200
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:47,920
'A salmon!' cried Philippa, staring at the 
parcel. There was now a small pool around it,  

201
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:52,480
spreading over the floor. 'But 
that's whiskey! Can't you smell it?'

202
00:19:53,760 --> 00:20:00,640
The servant came respectfully forward. He 
knelt down, and cautiously picked pieces  

203
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:06,960
of a broken glass bottle out of the brown 
paper. The smell of whiskey became stronger.

204
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:14,560
'I'm afraid the other things are ruined, sir,' 
he said seriously, and pulled out of the parcel,  

205
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:18,560
one after the other, a very 
large pair of dancing shoes,  

206
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:22,800
two long grey stockings, and a 
pair of grass-green breeches.

207
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:30,320
They were greeted with wild enthusiasm, in 
doubtless much the same way as when they  

208
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:36,240
shared the success of Mr Jimmy Durkan at 
the Feis, but Alice Hervey was not amused.

209
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:44,320
'You know, dear,' she said to Philippa 
afterwards, 'I don't think it was very clever  

210
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:52,000
of dear Sinclair to take the wrong 
parcel. I had wanted that salmon.'
 
 
 
 

211
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:52,553
- THE END -

